        "content": [
          {
            "type": "output_text",
            "text": "**Rust**  \nSentiment is mixed, with strong praise for memory safety, performance, type system, and suitability for systems/AI/agentic coding, tempered by frustrations over slow compile times, painful rust-analyzer on large codebases, messy async, and perceived complexity or weak stdlib.[[1]](https://x.com/rednafi/status/2076982197542588822)[[2]](https://x.com/ashu210890/status/2076998985315963310)[[3]](https://x.com/AutisticOvrflow/status/2078372062347829360)[[4]](https://x.com/Citrullin/status/2078473150942081515) Top concern is tooling/compile-time friction and async ergonomics. Momentum is rising, shown by new fan conversions, learning series, production projects (e.g., native Rust apps), and AI code-gen endorsements.[[5]](https://x.com/_NakulBhardwaj_/status/2078721202873655730)[[6]](https://x.com/drbaph/status/2077928560946184305)\n\n**TypeScript**  \nSentiment is positive, highlighting superior safety, tooling, refactoring ease, scalability over plain JS, popularity growth (noted as 3rd most popular), and better AI-generated code support.[[7]](https://x.com/icookandcode/status/2076322945626980550)[[8]](https://x.com/SweetTechAZ/status/2078179991859151283)[[9]](https://x.com/swapnakpanda/status/2077827900271894737) Top concern is overly complex type definitions (often leading to `any` casts), plus runtime performance and npm ecosystem risks for non-frontend use.[[10]](https://x.com/lhk_SE/status/2078396346562756827)[[11]](https://x.com/Radicalbyte343/status/2078251984394588416) Momentum is rising amid widespread adoption in full-stack/web/AI contexts and ongoing feature evolution.[[7]](https://x.com/icookandcode/status/2076322945626980550)\n\n**Go**  \nSentiment is mixed: lauded for simplicity, predictability, high performance in networking/microservices (e.g., throughput gains), enterprise maintainability, and \"boring\" suitability for AI-generated code, but criticized for verbosity, poor error handling, missing enums/true generics polish, nils, and restrictive feel that reduces expressiveness.[[12]](https://x.com/Hi_Mrinal/status/2077371600622756202)[[13]](https://x.com/prints_twt/status/2076397279246954869)[[14]](https://x.com/rseroter/status/2078122550186705233)[[15]](https://x.com/danielBrenot/status/2078703557155369438) Top concern is verbose error handling (`if err != nil`) and limited modern features. Momentum is stable, with steady project-sharing, learning posts, and recognition in cloud/AI-era contexts without major hype spikes or declines.[[16]](https://x.com/Greegman/status/2076734012635463791)[[17]](https://x.com/fromcodetocloud/status/2078049276274614513)",
